    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix SIB3 and SIB5 dump functions to correctly interpret 3GPP values\n\n### Summary\nThe `dump_sib3()` and `dump_sib5()` functions in `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_UE.c` were incorrectly interpreting 3GPP specification values for q_Hyst and speed state scaling factors (sf_Medium/sf_High). This caused misleading debug output when displaying SIB3/SIB5 information.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_UE.c`: Fixed q_Hyst mapping to use proper 3GPP TS 36.331 values (0-24 dB range)\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_UE.c`: Corrected speed state scaling factor interpretation for both SIB3 and SIB5\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_UE.c`: Updated logging format to show both raw and decoded values\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running OAI UE with logging enabled, the SIB3 dump would show incorrect dB values for q_Hyst and speed state scaling factors. For example, a raw q_Hyst value of 7 (which should decode to 8 dB) was incorrectly shown as 14 dB. Similarly, speed state scaling factors were not properly mapped to their dB equivalents (-6 to 0 dB range).\n\nAfter this fix, the logged values correctly reflect the 3GPP specification mappings, making the debug output accurate and useful for network analysis.\n"
}